### `[NEW]` `app/api/column_router.py`
New FastAPI router with prefix `/lineage/columns`, tag `"column-lineage"`. Three endpoints:

#### `GET /lineage/columns/{dataset_uri}`
Returns all columns belonging to a dataset.
```
Cypher: MATCH (c:Column {dataset_uri: $uri}) RETURN c
Response: { dataset_uri, columns: [{uri, name}] }
404 if dataset does not exist in Neo4j
```

#### `GET /lineage/column-upstream/{column_uri}`
Returns everything upstream of a column (what feeds into it).
```
Cypher:
MATCH path = (start:Column {uri: $uri})<-[:TRANSFORMS*1..10]-(upstream:Column)
RETURN DISTINCT upstream, relationships(path)

Response: { column_uri, upstream_columns: [{uri, name, dataset_uri, via_job}] }
404 if column not found
```

#### `GET /lineage/column-impact/{column_uri}`
Returns all downstream columns that would break if this column changes.
```
Cypher:
MATCH path = (start:Column {uri: $uri})-[:TRANSFORMS*1..10]->(downstream:Column)
RETURN DISTINCT downstream, relationships(path)

Response: { column_uri, impacted_columns: [{uri, name, dataset_uri, via_job}], impact_score }
404 if column not found
```

