## Pipeline File Format (Contract)

Every file in `pipelines/` must export these exact names. This is the **pipeline contract**:

```python
# pipelines/ecommerce.py

PIPELINE_NAME = "ecommerce"
PIPELINE_DESCRIPTION = "E-commerce order processing pipeline"
NAMESPACE = "postgres://ecommerce"
ORCHESTRATOR = "dbt"
EVENT_DELAY_SECONDS = 2.0
DEFAULT_SEARCH_URI = f"{NAMESPACE}/final_orders"
DEFAULT_SEARCH_DIRECTION = "upstream"

PIPELINE_JOBS = [
    {
        "job_name": "load_raw_orders",
        "description": "Load raw orders from S3",
        "inputs":  [(NAMESPACE, "s3_raw_orders")],
        "outputs": [(NAMESPACE, "raw_orders")],
        "column_mappings": [
            ("s3_raw_orders", "order_id",    "raw_orders", "id"),
            ("s3_raw_orders", "user_id",     "raw_orders", "customer_id"),
            ("s3_raw_orders", "order_total", "raw_orders", "total"),
        ]
    },
    # ... more jobs
]
```

No other interface required. No base class, no inheritance. Just a Python file with these variables.

