## `[NEW]` `pipeline_registry.py`

Central registry that auto-discovers all pipeline files. Contains:

```
PIPELINE_DIR = Path(__file__).parent / "pipelines"

function get_all_pipelines() -> dict[str, module]:
    Scans PIPELINE_DIR for .py files (excluding __init__.py)
    Imports each as a module using importlib
    Returns dict: { pipeline_name: module }
    E.g: { "jaffle_shop": <module>, "ecommerce": <module> }

function get_pipeline(name: str) -> module:
    Returns specific pipeline module by PIPELINE_NAME
    Raises ValueError if not found (with list of available names)

function list_pipeline_names() -> list[str]:
    Returns sorted list of all available PIPELINE_NAME values
```

